history.content:
The google form was for the interest of the instructors and to help them plan. It did not cause one to be moved.  Since the number of interested students in various prioritized categories (all of which need the course for their major) with interest in taking the class may exceed the class capacity, it can't be guaranteed that all of each category of student is able to take it in a particular semester. 

It does look like estimations of how many students from each category would attempt to enroll (and choose a lab with capacity) were a little off so I have re-adjusted and added additional capacity for 1st year EECS majors. You should be processed off the waitlist by noon. If not, please email ee-scheduling@berkeley.edu and include your SID and that you are an EECS 1st year student.

children.subject: Class capacity is rapidly filling up. My response earlier assumed you had already moved yourself to the lite lab (999L) waitlist. It won't move students into full labs.
Oh I see! I dropped my previous enrollment and moved myself to the lite lab so I am now enrolled in the class. Thanks for your help!!

Thanks for your response! Unfortunately it looks like I’m still on the waitlist... I’ve emailed the scheduling address and am hoping to hear back soon. My friend dropped the class with a regular lab and then re-enrolled but in the lite lab, and she got in. Should I just do that/will that work for me?

history.content:
Hi, I’m a freshman in EECS and I phase 1’d 16B the exact minute my enrollment opened (Oct 28... ) and selected Lite Lab on the Google Form sent out but I’m still currently 223 on the waitlist. I just got an email that the remaining available seats are reserved and I don’t meet any requirements in those seats. Is there anything I can do (any way to get special permission etc.)? 

I recall Prof. Ranade saying in 16A that they were trying to ensure that every freshman wanting to take 16B could - is that still a possibility? I’m getting pretty nervous since I really want to learn the material and I need the course for my major. 

I appreciate any help. Thanks!
